---
title: Root causes of unreliable production releases
---
ishikawa-beta
  Unreliable production releases
    People
      Ownership changes during incidents
      Critical knowledge held by one engineer
      Review load exceeds team capacity
    Process
      Acceptance criteria are ambiguous
      Risky changes bypass staging
      Rollback steps are not rehearsed
      Release windows keep moving
    Platform
      Test environments drift from production
      Deployments are slow
        Images are rebuilt repeatedly
        Database migrations block startup
      Feature flags lack lifecycle controls
    Product
      Scope changes after implementation starts
      Dependencies cross several teams
      Edge cases are discovered by customers
    Partners
      Vendor sandboxes behave differently
      Rate limits are undocumented
      Status notifications arrive late
    Measurement
      Flaky tests hide real regressions
      Service-level indicators are incomplete
      Release health has no shared scorecard
